Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:02.77,中文,,0,0,0,,有种感觉 派对才刚刚开始{\r英文}\NGot a feeling the party's just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.44,0:04:07.18,中文,,0,0,0,,-开张快乐 King -开张快乐 Pride{\r英文}\N- Happy grand opening, King! - Happy grand opening, Pride!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:10.88,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 他会很喜欢的{\r英文}\NOh, he's gonna just love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.88,0:04:12.78,中文,,0,0,0,,Patton在哪儿 他应该带来{\r英文}\NWhere's Patton? He's supposed to bring
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.79,0:04:14.09,中文,,0,0,0,,Randazzo's(品牌名)的帝王蛋糕{\r英文}\Nthe King Cake from Randazzo's.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.09,0:04:15.25,中文,,0,0,0,,打过电话了{\r英文}\NCalled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.26,0:04:16.42,中文,,0,0,0,,他迟到了{\r英文}\NLate. Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.42,0:04:18.19,中文,,0,0,0,,找到帝王蛋糕里的{\r英文}\NFinding that little baby
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:20.22,中文,,0,0,0,,那个小东西，这是另一个我喜欢的{\r英文}\Ninside the King Cake, yet another New Orleans tradition
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.23,0:04:21.89,中文,,0,0,0,,-新奥尔良的传统 -对吧{\r英文}\N- that I love! - Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.90,0:04:23.83,中文,,0,0,0,,-太可爱了 -只不过狂欢节{\r英文}\N- It's so sweet. - Only Mardi Gras
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.83,0:04:25.13,中文,,0,0,0,,不是起于新奥尔良{\r英文}\Ndidn't start in New Orleans.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.13,0:04:26.56,中文,,0,0,0,,而是起于阿拉巴马州{\r英文}\NIt started in Alabama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:27.60,中文,,0,0,0,,胡说{\r英文}\NShut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:29.17,中文,,0,0,0,,真的 传说莫比尔{\r英文}\NYeah the lore is Mobile had
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:29.17,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}位于美国阿拉巴马州
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.17,0:04:31.80,中文,,0,0,0,,远在新奥尔良之前就有大型派对和游行了{\r英文}\Nthe big parties and big floats way before New Orleans.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.81,0:04:32.80,中文,,0,0,0,,传说而已{\r英文}\N"The lore"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:38.94,中文,,0,0,0,,在Landon Court酒店{\r英文}\NDead Marine and a wounded security guard
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.95,0:04:40.18,中文,,0,0,0,,一名海军死亡 一个保安受伤{\r英文}\Nat Landon Court Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.18,0:04:41.75,中文,,0,0,0,,今晚那里有市长的狂欢宴{\r英文}\NMayor's Soirée is there tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.75,0:04:43.38,中文,,0,0,0,,我的邀请函一定是{\r英文}\NWell, my invitation must've
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:44.65,中文,,0,0,0,,在邮寄过程中丢失了{\r英文}\Ngotten lost in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.65,0:04:45.88,中文,,0,0,0,,显然是的{\r英文}\NClearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.89,0:04:47.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是啊 街上全是人{\r英文}\NYeah, streets are packed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:48.65,中文,,0,0,0,,走过去更方便{\r英文}\NBe easier to walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.66,0:04:50.49,中文,,0,0,0,,我去找Pride 到那儿跟你们汇合{\r英文}\NI'll get Pride and meet you guys there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.36,0:04:55.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我只想郑重声明一句{\r英文}\NJust like to go on record as saying
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:57.63,中文,,0,0,0,,这不是我派对的风格{\r英文}\Nthis is not my kind of party.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.53,0:05:03.90,中文,,0,0,0,,不管你是谁{\r英文}\NWell, whoever you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.90,0:05:06.17,中文,,0,0,0,,都等着下地狱吧{\r英文}\Nall hell is coming in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.17,0:05:07.87,中文,,0,0,0,,绑架市长{\r英文}\NThe Mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.87,0:05:09.37,中文,,0,0,0,,和一个联邦探员{\r英文}\N...and a Fed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.38,0:05:11.44,中文,,0,0,0,,这真是{\r英文}\NThat is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:13.34,中文,,0,0,0,,真是一个糟糕的计划 孩子{\r英文}\Nthat is some poor planning, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.35,0:05:14.58,中文,,0,0,0,,糟糕的计划{\r英文}\NPoor planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:16.51,中文,,0,0,0,,我不这么认为{\r英文}\NI'm not sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.52,0:05:18.85,中文,,0,0,0,,这样的绑架需要时间准备{\r英文}\NSomething like this takes time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.85,0:05:21.29,中文,,0,0,0,,需要配合{\r英文}\NCoordination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.59,0:05:26.86,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 那个红裙子的女孩{\r英文}\NOh, the girl in the red dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:28.66,中文,,0,0,0,,女孩{\r英文}\N"Girl"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:31.66,中文,,0,0,0,,她是你的搭档 对吧{\r英文}\NShe's your partner, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.70,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么了 这些话太贬低她了吗{\r英文}\NWhat's the matter-- these digs too low-brow for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.70,0:05:35.27,中文,,0,0,0,,是吗{\r英文}\NIs that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.67,0:05:40.74,中文,,0,0,0,,她是一个... 选民{\r英文}\NShe's a... constituent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.74,0:05:44.24,中文,,0,0,0,,想和我私下会面{\r英文}\NWanted a private meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.68,0:05:50.28,中文,,0,0,0,,你愿意让我们怎么称呼你{\r英文}\NIs there some way you'd like us to address you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.42,0:05:57.05,中文,,0,0,0,,你有名字么{\r英文}\NYou got a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.06,0:05:58.86,中文,,0,0,0,,搞什么鬼 Dwayne{\r英文}\NWhat the hell, Dwayne?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.46,0:06:01.79,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride{\r英文}\NHey, Pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:03.09,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride{\r英文}\NPride?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.20,0:06:08.00,中文,,0,0,0,,-他奋力抵抗了 -什么{\r英文}\N- He put up a fight. - Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:10.43,中文,,0,0,0,,就在你鞋子踩着的位置{\r英文}\NRight about where your loafers are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.44,0:06:11.77,中文,,0,0,0,,丢下这个东西的人么{\r英文}\NThe man who dropped this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.77,0:06:13.64,中文,,0,0,0,,我卖艺赚钱{\r英文}\NI busk for tips.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:16.31,中文,,0,0,0,,狂欢节是我最忙的一晚{\r英文}\NMardi Gras is my busiest night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:18.41,中文,,0,0,0,,我出来小憩之时{\r英文}\NI was just taking a break
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.41,0:06:20.78,中文,,0,0,0,,看见一个戴着面具的男人{\r英文}\Nwhen I saw this guy in a mask
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.78,0:06:23.95,中文,,0,0,0,,用那个扎了他{\r英文}\Nhit him with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.95,0:06:27.75,中文,,0,0,0,,然后把他推进了一辆车{\r英文}\Nand then shove him in a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.75,0:06:29.95,中文,,0,0,0,,你看到车牌了么{\r英文}\NYou get a license plate?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.60,0:06:45.14,中文,,0,0,0,,看见什么人靠近尸体吗 有目击者吗{\r英文}\NSee anyone near the body? Any witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.14,0:06:48.61,中文,,0,0,0,,没有 死者是酒店保安{\r英文}\NNo, and the deceased was working for hotel security.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.61,0:06:50.71,中文,,0,0,0,,为这次市长的活动来做兼职 但他{\r英文}\NMoonlighting for the Mayor's event, but he--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.71,0:06:52.61,中文,,0,0,0,,他不是我们的人{\r英文}\Nhe's not one of ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.61,0:06:54.41,中文,,0,0,0,,-你是 -Kelly Grace{\r英文}\N- And you are? - Kelly Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.41,0:06:56.01,中文,,0,0,0,,市长的新闻发言人{\r英文}\NMayor's press secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.02,0:06:59.12,中文,,0,0,0,,这位是Tom Bujei 幕僚长 还有Brad Curry是...{\r英文}\NThis is Tom Bujei, Chief of Staff and Brad Curry is--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.12,0:07:00.45,中文,,0,0,0,,Brad Curry 市长的代理律师{\r英文}\NBrad Curry, Mayor's Deputy Counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:01.92,中文,,0,0,0,,是我联系的联邦探员{\r英文}\NI'm the one who contacted the Feds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:04.92,中文,,0,0,0,,稍等 Brad 我们遇到更大的问题...{\r英文}\NHang on, Brad, okay, we have bigger problems--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.92,0:07:07.63,中文,,0,0,0,,问题就在那躺着 Tom 那个死了的海军{\r英文}\NThe problem is lying right in there, Tom-- the dead Marine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.63,0:07:10.09,中文,,0,0,0,,好了 大家都少说一句{\r英文}\NOkay, everyone just take a step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.10,0:07:13.60,中文,,0,0,0,,Curry先生 让保安封锁酒店{\r英文}\NLook, Mr. Curry, tell the security to lock down the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:15.03,中文,,0,0,0,,任何人不得进出 谢谢{\r英文}\NNo one in or out. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:18.17,中文,,0,0,0,,Loretta女士{\r英文}\NMs. Loretta?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.17,0:07:20.81,中文,,0,0,0,,恩 是军用证件{\r英文}\NUh, it's military I.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.81,0:07:24.71,中文,,0,0,0,,他是Jason Alex下士 隶属Bell Chase基地{\r英文}\NHe's Corporal Jason Alex, stationed at Bell Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.71,0:07:27.68,中文,,0,0,0,,死因呢{\r英文}\NCause of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.18,0:07:31.12,中文,,0,0,0,,就是这里面的东西{\r英文}\NWhatever was in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.12,0:07:34.72,中文,,0,0,0,,可能和用在Tate官员身上的药一样{\r英文}\NMight be the same thing that drugged Officer Tate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:36.82,中文,,0,0,0,,Tate官员{\r英文}\NOfficer Tate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.82,0:07:38.46,中文,,0,0,0,,你能告诉我发生了什么吗{\r英文}\Ncan you tell me what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:43.06,中文,,0,0,0,,我看见一个穿红色裙子的女人跑过{\r英文}\NI saw the woman in the red dress run by.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.06,0:07:45.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我回去找MONO{\r英文}\NI went back to find MONO.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.16,0:07:47.53,中文,,0,0,0,,然后就感到脖子上一阵剧痛{\r英文}\NAnd I felt a sharp pain in my neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.53,0:07:48.50,中文,,0,0,0,,什么是MONO{\r英文}\N"MONO"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.50,0:07:50.17,中文,,0,0,0,,新奥尔良的市长{\r英文}\NMayor of New Orleans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.81,0:07:58.28,中文,,0,0,0,,那是他的手机 我知道这铃声{\r英文}\NThat's his phone. I recognize the ringtone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.28,0:07:59.94,中文,,0,0,0,,市长的手机{\r英文}\NThe Mayor's phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.95,0:08:00.91,中文,,0,0,0,,对 就是他的{\r英文}\NYes, it's his.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.91,0:08:03.05,中文,,0,0,0,,-他不见了 -喂{\r英文}\N- He's missing. - Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.05,0:08:04.82,中文,,0,0,0,,我们认为他被绑架了{\r英文}\NWe think he may have been kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.82,0:08:05.98,中文,,0,0,0,,等等{\r英文}\NWait--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.99,0:08:07.59,中文,,0,0,0,,Brody 你说什么{\r英文}\NBrody, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.36,0:08:10.72,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么了{\r英文}\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:13.72,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride也被掳走了{\r英文}\NPride's been taken, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.06,0:08:18.30,中文,,0,0,0,,我们做了什么{\r英文}\NWhat did we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.30,0:08:19.43,中文,,0,0,0,,不知道{\r英文}\NDon't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:21.97,中文,,0,0,0,,可能什么也没做{\r英文}\NMaybe nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:25.90,中文,,0,0,0,,无论怎样{\r英文}\NWell, either way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.91,0:08:28.01,中文,,0,0,0,,有很多人爱我们 所以{\r英文}\Na lot of folks love us, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.01,0:08:31.11,中文,,0,0,0,,他们肯定发现我们不见了{\r英文}\Nthey must've noticed that we're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:33.11,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么{\r英文}\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.11,0:08:34.55,中文,,0,0,0,,狂欢节{\r英文}\NMardi Gras?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.55,0:08:36.88,中文,,0,0,0,,-哦 -所以...{\r英文}\N- Oh. - So...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.22,中文,,0,0,0,,这相机是干什么的{\r英文}\NI mean, what is the camera for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.22,0:08:41.99,中文,,0,0,0,,那是什么啊{\r英文}\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:45.66,中文,,0,0,0,,除非{\r英文}\NUnless, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.66,0:08:48.13,中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得是恐怖分子么{\r英文}\Ndo you think it's-it's terrorism?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.13,0:08:49.66,中文,,0,0,0,,是恐怖分子么{\r英文}\NIs it terrorism?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:51.36,中文,,0,0,0,,-市长先生... -是恐怖分子 对吧{\r英文}\N- Mr. Mayor, you-- - It's terrorism, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:53.36,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿{\r英文}\NHey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.37,0:08:57.87,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿 所以你才把我朋友跟我关在一起 是不是{\r英文}\NHey, so is that why you have D-man out here with me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.87,0:08:59.27,中文,,0,0,0,,-Douglas -就我们俩吗{\r英文}\N- Douglas... - Two of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.27,0:09:00.57,中文,,0,0,0,,你是恐怖分子吗{\r英文}\NAre you a damn terrorist?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.57,0:09:02.77,中文,,0,0,0,,你他妈的是恐怖分子吗{\r英文}\NAre you a damn terrorist?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.78,0:09:04.18,中文,,0,0,0,,冷静{\r英文}\NCalm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.05,0:09:08.71,中文,,0,0,0,,我有很多富豪朋友 很多富豪朋友{\r英文}\NI got a lot of rich friends. Lot of rich friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:10.85,中文,,0,0,0,,你就直说你想要什么吧{\r英文}\NJust tell us what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.85,0:09:13.45,中文,,0,0,0,,先生{\r英文}\NSir?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.46,0:09:17.22,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么我们在这{\r英文}\NWhy are we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.23,0:09:21.13,中文,,0,0,0,,来认罪{\r英文}\NTo confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.79,0:09:43.69,中文,,0,0,0,,Patton 有什么进展{\r英文}\NAll right, Patton, what do we got?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.69,0:09:45.36,中文,,0,0,0,,等会儿 就一会儿{\r英文}\NWait, just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:46.39,中文,,0,0,0,,我等不了了{\r英文}\NOkay, can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.40,0:09:47.36,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride被绑架了{\r英文}\NPride's been kidnapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.36,0:09:48.60,中文,,0,0,0,,市长也被绑架了{\r英文}\Nthe Mayor's been kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:50.30,中文,,0,0,0,,多事之秋 懂我的意思吗{\r英文}\NCats and dogs-- know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.30,0:09:51.37,中文,,0,0,0,,谁在看着酒吧{\r英文}\NWell, who's watching the bar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.37,0:09:53.03,中文,,0,0,0,,一个满身涂成银色的街头艺人{\r英文}\NA silver-painted man
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:55.64,中文,,0,0,0,,还有一百来个Pride的好朋友{\r英文}\Nand about a hundred of Pride's closest friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.64,0:09:56.94,中文,,0,0,0,,多事之秋{\r英文}\NCats and dogs?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.94,0:09:58.67,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧{\r英文}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.67,0:10:00.87,中文,,0,0,0,,市长跟一个NCIS探员{\r英文}\NThe Mayor and an NCIS agent
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.88,0:10:02.74,中文,,0,0,0,,在狂欢节被绑架了{\r英文}\Nget kidnapped on Mardi Gras.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.75,0:10:04.58,中文,,0,0,0,,这不可能是个巧合{\r英文}\NThis is too much of a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:07.41,中文,,0,0,0,,可能是有人想要传达什么信息{\r英文}\NMaybe someone trying to send a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.42,0:10:08.82,中文,,0,0,0,,我查了Pride的手机{\r英文}\NI dumped Pride's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:10.25,中文,,0,0,0,,没有恐吓电话{\r英文}\NNo threatening calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.25,0:10:12.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我跟联邦调查局 国土安全局都核对过{\r英文}\NI checked with FBI, Homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.25,0:10:15.19,中文,,0,0,0,,没有恐怖威胁 连传言都没有{\r英文}\NNo terror threats or chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.19,0:10:16.92,中文,,0,0,0,,那是他们俩都认识的人么{\r英文}\NSomeone they both know then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.93,0:10:20.16,中文,,0,0,0,,也许是旧案中的一个嫌疑犯{\r英文}\NMaybe-maybe a suspect from a past case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.16,0:10:21.66,中文,,0,0,0,,我会把以前的案子都找出来{\r英文}\NI'll pull old cases and cross-reference them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.66,0:10:22.86,中文,,0,0,0,,跟Hamilton交叉比对{\r英文}\Nwith Hamilton.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:24.87,中文,,0,0,0,,好的 那位满身银色的朋友{\r英文}\NAll right, my-my silver-painted friend
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.87,0:10:28.30,中文,,0,0,0,,说他看见了一辆灰色的福特轿车 车牌号是TSJ{\r英文}\Nsaid he saw a gray Ford sedan, license plate TSJ.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.30,0:10:30.27,中文,,0,0,0,,追踪它 全国通缉{\r英文}\NTrack it, wide BOLO.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:32.71,中文,,0,0,0,,公路 高速 机场{\r英文}\NRoads, highways, airports.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.71,0:10:34.17,中文,,0,0,0,,好 我这就办{\r英文}\NOkay, I'm on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.18,0:10:36.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经跟联邦调查局申请了支援{\r英文}\NI called the FBI for support.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.21,0:10:38.41,中文,,0,0,0,,他们至少还要一个小时 因为交通堵塞{\r英文}\NThey're at least an hour out, 'cause of traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:40.05,中文,,0,0,0,,等等 如果他们进不来{\r英文}\NWait, if they can't get in,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.05,0:10:42.12,中文,,0,0,0,,那我们的绑架者可能也出不去{\r英文}\Nthen maybe our-our kidnapper wasn't able to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.12,0:10:45.52,中文,,0,0,0,,正在查街边监控 寻找这辆灰色轿车{\r英文}\NCracking street cams. Looking for this gray sedan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.52,0:10:46.75,中文,,0,0,0,,这得花点时间{\r英文}\NIt's gonna take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.76,0:10:47.99,中文,,0,0,0,,我们没有时间了{\r英文}\NOkay, we don't have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.99,0:10:49.59,中文,,0,0,0,,绑架的第一个小时是至关重要的{\r英文}\NFirst hour of a kidnapping is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.59,0:10:51.19,中文,,0,0,0,,就在这一个小时 情况可能失去控制{\r英文}\NIt's when things can go from bad to worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.19,0:10:52.69,中文,,0,0,0,,你以为我不知道么{\r英文}\NYou don't think I know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.53,0:10:54.90,中文,,0,0,0,,我们会找到他的{\r英文}\NWe're gonna find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:10:59.63,中文,,0,0,0,,有人出来承认绑架么{\r英文}\N{\i1}Anyone claim responsibility?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.64,0:11:00.83,中文,,0,0,0,,有要求赎金么{\r英文}\NAny ransom demands?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:02.74,中文,,0,0,0,,现在只接到媒体的电话{\r英文}\NThe only calls are from the press.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.74,0:11:04.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他们想在市长和游行国王握手前{\r英文}\NThey want to talk to the Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.44,0:11:05.74,中文,,0,0,0,,跟他谈谈{\r英文}\Nbefore he shakes the parade king's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.74,0:11:07.74,中文,,0,0,0,,距离握手还有不到一个小时{\r英文}\NWhich is less than an hour away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.74,0:11:09.58,中文,,0,0,0,,所以解决这事儿{\r英文}\NSo it would be great to resolve this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.58,0:11:11.45,中文,,0,0,0,,越早越好{\r英文}\Nsooner than later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.45,0:11:14.28,中文,,0,0,0,,对不起 但事关重大{\r英文}\NLook, I'm sorry, but it's a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.28,0:11:16.35,中文,,0,0,0,,Curry 你是代理律师 对吧{\r英文}\NCurry, you're deputy counsel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.35,0:11:19.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你知道有什么反对市长的言论么{\r英文}\NKnow of any claims against the Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.26,0:11:20.65,中文,,0,0,0,,有没有愤怒的人{\r英文}\NAnyone who's angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.66,0:11:21.89,中文,,0,0,0,,没有 你为什么认为{\r英文}\NNo, and what makes you think
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.89,0:11:23.06,中文,,0,0,0,,这事儿不是因为你们的人{\r英文}\Nthis isn't about your guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:25.26,中文,,0,0,0,,我们可以稍后讨论是谁的问题{\r英文}\NWell, we can debate character later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.26,0:11:28.46,中文,,0,0,0,,现在 我们最大的希望在于找到这个女孩{\r英文}\NAll right, our best chance is to find this girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.46,0:11:31.13,中文,,0,0,0,,你们有谁认识她么 跟她说过话{\r英文}\NDo any of you know her? Talk to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.13,0:11:32.50,中文,,0,0,0,,天啊 没有{\r英文}\NGod, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.50,0:11:34.30,中文,,0,0,0,,她知道在哪里下手{\r英文}\NShe knew just where to take him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.30,0:11:35.60,中文,,0,0,0,,在那个凹室里没有监控{\r英文}\NNo surveillance in that alcove.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:38.57,中文,,0,0,0,,那附近有一个服务通道{\r英文}\NThere's a service entrance nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.28,0:11:40.54,中文,,0,0,0,,Loretta女士{\r英文}\NMs. Loretta?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.54,0:11:42.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你还在这{\r英文}\NYou still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.18,0:11:43.34,中文,,0,0,0,,现在是狂欢节{\r英文}\NIt's Mardi Gras.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.35,0:11:44.98,中文,,0,0,0,,我的警卫需要另一个警卫{\r英文}\NMy police escort needs a police escort
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.98,0:11:47.51,中文,,0,0,0,,来帮我把Alex下士送到停尸间{\r英文}\Nto help me get Corporal Alex to the morgue.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.52,0:11:49.02,中文,,0,0,0,,不过 我在等的时候{\r英文}\NBut, while I wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.02,0:11:51.55,中文,,0,0,0,,你看到眼睛周围的肿胀和僵硬么{\r英文}\Nyou see this swelling and rigidity around the eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.55,0:11:54.56,中文,,0,0,0,,可能是被注射药物带来的反应{\r英文}\NCould be a reaction to the drug he was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:56.02,中文,,0,0,0,,我们找出是哪种药物{\r英文}\NWe find out what kind of drug,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.03,0:11:58.03,中文,,0,0,0,,就能查到谁可以获得这种药物{\r英文}\Nand we figure out who had access to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.03,0:11:59.73,中文,,0,0,0,,我会把它给Sebastian 让他开工{\r英文}\NI'll get it to Sebastian, get him started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.73,0:12:01.10,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 随时告诉我进展{\r英文}\NThank you. Keep me posted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.10,0:12:02.43,中文,,0,0,0,,有发现{\r英文}\NGot something!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.67,0:12:06.27,中文,,0,0,0,,我想这是MONO的妹子{\r英文}\NI think this is MONO's girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.27,0:12:07.37,中文,,0,0,0,,看这个穿着大衣的女孩{\r英文}\NSee the chick in the coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.37,0:12:08.64,中文,,0,0,0,,红色亮片 就是她{\r英文}\NRed sequins, that's her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.87,0:12:11.27,中文,,0,0,0,,很好 我们负责宴会厅{\r英文}\NGood. All right, we'll take the ballroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.27,0:12:12.94,中文,,0,0,0,,你的人负责底层{\r英文}\NYour team has the floors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:14.81,中文,,0,0,0,,我把这个发给Patton 看能不能确认身份{\r英文}\NI'll get this over to Patton, see if can get an I.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.81,0:12:16.11,中文,,0,0,0,,等等{\r英文}\NWait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.11,0:12:17.88,中文,,0,0,0,,最好别让太多人卷进来{\r英文}\NBest not to involve too many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:19.91,中文,,0,0,0,,我们不想在狂欢节诱发全市恐慌{\r英文}\NI mean, we don't want a citywide panic on Mardi Gras.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:21.82,中文,,0,0,0,,还有 在我们弄清楚眼前的情况之前{\r英文}\NAbsolutely, we need to keep this out of the glare of the media
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.82,0:12:23.62,中文,,0,0,0,,绝对不能让媒体注意到{\r英文}\Nuntil we know what we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.62,0:12:24.92,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿 帮个忙{\r英文}\NHey, do us a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.92,0:12:26.59,中文,,0,0,0,,别担心公关问题了{\r英文}\NStop worrying about the PR.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.92,0:12:26.59,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Public Relations
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.59,0:12:29.59,中文,,0,0,0,,担心担心市长和Pride的生命安全吧{\r英文}\NAnd start worrying about the Mayor and Pride's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.76,0:12:37.83,中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得会不会是什么{\r英文}\NDo you think this is some sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.83,0:12:40.90,中文,,0,0,0,,奇怪的仪式之类的{\r英文}\Nweird ritual or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.90,0:12:44.30,中文,,0,0,0,,现在是狂欢节 "圣灰星期三"的前夜{\r英文}\NIt's Mardi Gras-- it's the night before Ash Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.90,0:12:44.30,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}基督教四旬期首日
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.31,0:12:46.27,中文,,0,0,0,,每个人都要赎罪{\r英文}\NEverybody's got to atone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:47.71,中文,,0,0,0,,从时机看 倒是挺对的{\r英文}\NTiming does seem right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:49.51,中文,,0,0,0,,我们应该认什么罪{\r英文}\NWell, what are we supposed to be confessing to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这人到底是谁啊{\r英文}\NI mean, who is this guy, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.28,0:12:52.78,中文,,0,0,0,,是被你惹怒的毒贩么{\r英文}\NIs he some drug dealer that you pissed off?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.78,0:12:55.18,中文,,0,0,0,,他是不是间谍之类的{\r英文}\NIs he a spy or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.18,0:12:58.19,中文,,0,0,0,,不能确定他和NCIS有关系{\r英文}\NNot sure he's an NCIS interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:13:00.49,中文,,0,0,0,,他在那后面干什么{\r英文}\NWhat is he doing back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.49,0:13:03.26,中文,,0,0,0,,Douglas? Douglas...{\r英文}\NDouglas? Douglas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:05.93,中文,,0,0,0,,听我说 你得让我来跟他聊{\r英文}\Nlisten to me-- you need to let me do the talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:08.63,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 你看 你又瞧不起我了 Dwayne{\r英文}\NOh, see, there you go selling me short again, Dwayne.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:10.30,中文,,0,0,0,,人们喜欢跟我谈话{\r英文}\NPeople like talking to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.30,0:13:11.97,中文,,0,0,0,,他们告诉我很多事情{\r英文}\NThey tell me a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.97,0:13:13.60,中文,,0,0,0,,你以为我是怎么当上市长的{\r英文}\NHow do you think I became Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.60,0:13:17.30,中文,,0,0,0,,另一个候选人让你的选区毒品泛滥{\r英文}\NThe other candidate was flooding your district with drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.60,0:13:17.30,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}S02E06的情节
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.31,0:13:20.91,中文,,0,0,0,,呃 我现在不想说这个{\r英文}\NYeah, well, I don't feel like talking about that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.91,0:13:21.98,中文,,0,0,0,,-真的 -嗯{\r英文}\N- Really? - Yeah--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:23.48,中文,,0,0,0,,闭嘴{\r英文}\NShut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:26.65,中文,,0,0,0,,该认罪了{\r英文}\NTime to confess!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.65,0:13:29.22,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你能告诉我们是什么罪 会有所帮助{\r英文}\NBe helpful if you could tell us what we were guilty of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.22,0:13:31.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得我们有什么罪{\r英文}\NWhat you{\i1} think{\i} we're guilty of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.49,0:13:35.82,中文,,0,0,0,,对你来说只是个笑话 是吗{\r英文}\NThis is all a joke to you, isn't it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.82,0:13:37.52,中文,,0,0,0,,市长{\r英文}\NMayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.53,0:13:41.46,中文,,0,0,0,,Douglas Hamilton 离异 有两个孩子{\r英文}\NDouglas Hamilton, divorced, two kids--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:43.80,中文,,0,0,0,,Max和Sam 都在里奇菲尔德预科学校{\r英文}\NMax and Sam, both at Ridgefield Prep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.80,0:13:45.37,中文,,0,0,0,,Dwayne Pride探员{\r英文}\NAgent Dwayne Pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.37,0:13:46.80,中文,,0,0,0,,同样离异{\r英文}\NAlso divorced,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:47.94,中文,,0,0,0,,喜欢睡在办公室{\r英文}\Nlikes to sleep at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.94,0:13:49.67,中文,,0,0,0,,女儿Laurel在上大学{\r英文}\NDaughter Laurel is at college.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.67,0:13:52.04,中文,,0,0,0,,合住宿舍 23号房{\r英文}\NMain dorm, room 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.04,0:13:53.24,中文,,0,0,0,,你把他们怎么了{\r英文}\NWhat have you done with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.24,0:13:54.34,中文,,0,0,0,,别急 市长{\r英文}\NEasy, Mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.34,0:13:56.64,中文,,0,0,0,,你们的家人现在还很安全{\r英文}\NYour families are safe for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.65,0:13:58.31,中文,,0,0,0,,只要我能如愿{\r英文}\Nas long as I get what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.31,0:13:59.45,中文,,0,0,0,,不{\r英文}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:01.48,中文,,0,0,0,,我需要保证{\r英文}\NI want a guarantee.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.48,0:14:04.25,中文,,0,0,0,,否则我一个字都不会说{\r英文}\NAnd I'm not gonna say a word until I get one!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.56,0:14:12.23,中文,,0,0,0,,你认为是民兵组织{\r英文}\NYou think this is a militia?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.23,0:14:13.96,中文,,0,0,0,,也许Hamilton不小心卷进来了{\r英文}\NMaybe Hamilton's involved somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.96,0:14:15.43,中文,,0,0,0,,Patton没有任何发现{\r英文}\NWell, Patton didn't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:17.83,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride有跟你说过什么吗{\r英文}\NHas Pride been telling you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.83,0:14:19.27,中文,,0,0,0,,我 当然没有{\r英文}\NMe? Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:20.77,中文,,0,0,0,,你比我更了解他{\r英文}\NYou know him better than I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.77,0:14:23.50,中文,,0,0,0,,是 但他也会跟你聊{\r英文}\NYeah, well, he talks to you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.51,0:14:25.94,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride不见了 我很担心 好吗{\r英文}\NLook, Pride is gone. I'm worried, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.94,0:14:28.68,中文,,0,0,0,,是啊 我也一样{\r英文}\NYeah, so am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:30.44,中文,,0,0,0,,在心里{\r英文}\NOn the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.29,0:14:42.09,中文,,0,0,0,,红色亮片 12点方向{\r英文}\NRed sequins, 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:50.23,中文,,0,0,0,,噢 噢{\r英文}\NOh! Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.58,0:15:03.64,中文,,0,0,0,,联邦探员 站住{\r英文}\NFederal agents! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.32,0:15:07.81,中文,,0,0,0,,把刀放下{\r英文}\NPut the knife down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.82,0:15:09.98,中文,,0,0,0,,好{\r英文}\NSure...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.43,0:15:24.87,中文,,0,0,0,,他们到底在鼓什么掌{\r英文}\NWhat the hell are they clapping for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.87,0:15:27.23,中文,,0,0,0,,大概是因为我们仨{\r英文}\NI think the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.24,0:15:29.57,中文,,0,0,0,,我们每周二晚都会来{\r英文}\NWe'll be here every Tuesday night, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.57,0:15:31.87,中文,,0,0,0,,狂欢节快乐{\r英文}\NHappy Mardi Gras!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.31,0:15:38.88,中文,,0,0,0,,你现在还能脱身{\r英文}\NYou could leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:41.42,中文,,0,0,0,,放了我们{\r英文}\NFree us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.42,0:15:43.52,中文,,0,0,0,,我们没看见你的脸{\r英文}\NWe haven't even seen your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.52,0:15:45.75,中文,,0,0,0,,不知道你是谁{\r英文}\NDon't know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:48.02,中文,,0,0,0,,你想知道我是谁吗{\r英文}\NYou want to know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.02,0:15:51.29,中文,,0,0,0,,行啊 可以{\r英文}\NAll right, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.07,0:16:02.64,中文,,0,0,0,,认得我吗 市长{\r英文}\NRecognize me, Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.97,0:16:07.64,中文,,0,0,0,,但你认识 对吗 Pride探员{\r英文}\NBut you do, don't you, Agent Pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:15.12,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike Spar{\r英文}\NMike Spar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:16.68,中文,,0,0,0,,对{\r英文}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.69,0:16:19.19,中文,,0,0,0,,我记得{\r英文}\NI remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:21.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你们俩认识么{\r英文}\NYou two know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.19,0:16:24.99,中文,,0,0,0,,我还在警局时 我们见过{\r英文}\NWe met when I was with the sheriff's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.99,0:16:26.69,中文,,0,0,0,,25年前{\r英文}\N25 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.70,0:16:29.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我参与调查一个新奥尔良警方的案子{\r英文}\NGot looped into a NOPD case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:31.26,中文,,0,0,0,,受害人来自我所在的教区{\r英文}\NVictim was from my parish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.27,0:16:33.37,中文,,0,0,0,,我必须去递交死亡通知{\r英文}\NHad to deliver the death notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.37,0:16:36.34,中文,,0,0,0,,我的... 第一次{\r英文}\NMy... first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.34,0:16:37.77,中文,,0,0,0,,"您的夫人自杀身亡"{\r英文}\N"Your wife killed herself."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.77,0:16:40.04,中文,,0,0,0,,这是你当时说的话{\r英文}\NThat's what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.24,0:16:42.68,中文,,0,0,0,,我从未忘记你站在那儿{\r英文}\NI never forgot you standing there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.68,0:16:45.41,中文,,0,0,0,,手里抱着一个小女孩{\r英文}\Nwith that little girl in your arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.42,0:16:47.91,中文,,0,0,0,,我们在这儿是因为她{\r英文}\NShe's why we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.92,0:16:49.42,中文,,0,0,0,,你女儿么{\r英文}\NYour daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.99,0:16:55.39,中文,,0,0,0,,Stacey成长过程中 一直觉得是妈妈抛弃了她{\r英文}\NStacey grew up thinking her mom abandoned her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.39,0:16:59.13,中文,,0,0,0,,但我们都知道真相并非如此{\r英文}\NBut we know that's not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.13,0:17:00.83,中文,,0,0,0,,你和我{\r英文}\NYou and I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.83,0:17:04.06,中文,,0,0,0,,都知道是他杀了她{\r英文}\Nboth know that he murdered her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.57,0:17:26.97,中文,,0,0,0,,这其中一定有误会{\r英文}\NThis has got to be some mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.97,0:17:29.31,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride探员可能牵扯进了{\r英文}\NAgent Pride may have been involved
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:31.51,中文,,0,0,0,,你所想的事情{\r英文}\Nin whatever you think happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:33.25,中文,,0,0,0,,但与我无关{\r英文}\NBut not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.25,0:17:35.38,中文,,0,0,0,,25年前 我还在法学院读书{\r英文}\NI was in law school 25 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:39.32,中文,,0,0,0,,没错 还是Sigma Eta Omicron兄弟会的一员{\r英文}\NYes, and an alumni of Sigma Eta Omicron Fraternity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.32,0:17:42.29,中文,,0,0,0,,当时他们在Alastair酒店举办了狂欢派对{\r英文}\NThey had a Mardi Gras party at the Alastair Hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:44.29,中文,,0,0,0,,你的妻子去世当晚参加的派对{\r英文}\NParty your wife attended the night she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:45.56,中文,,0,0,0,,我记得{\r英文}\NI remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.56,0:17:46.79,中文,,0,0,0,,你当然记得{\r英文}\NOf course you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:50.10,中文,,0,0,0,,你曾参与掩盖真相{\r英文}\NYou were part of the cover-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.10,0:17:52.13,中文,,0,0,0,,那是你{\r英文}\NThat's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:53.57,中文,,0,0,0,,你曾参与案件调查{\r英文}\NYou were part of the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:17:54.93,中文,,0,0,0,,你当时在那儿{\r英文}\NYou were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.94,0:17:57.80,中文,,0,0,0,,我被通知前往一个自杀现场{\r英文}\NI was called to the scene of a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.81,0:18:00.17,中文,,0,0,0,,说是一个有抑郁症病史的女人{\r英文}\NTold a woman with a history of depression
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.17,0:18:03.78,中文,,0,0,0,,借兄弟会的派对来自杀{\r英文}\Nhad used a frat party as a means to end it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.78,0:18:05.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我 "我接受{\r英文}\NI... "I accept
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.21,0:18:07.18,中文,,0,0,0,,或者拒绝一个{\r英文}\N"or reject a hypothesis
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.18,0:18:09.05,中文,,0,0,0,,基于证据的假设"{\r英文}\Nbased on evidence."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.05,0:18:10.98,中文,,0,0,0,,科学家的信条{\r英文}\NScientist's creed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.99,0:18:12.75,中文,,0,0,0,,也应该是警察的信条{\r英文}\NShould be a cop's, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.75,0:18:17.22,中文,,0,0,0,,Hamilton所在兄弟会的五个成员的证词{\r英文}\NWitness statements from five of Hamilton's fraternity brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.22,0:18:19.69,中文,,0,0,0,,"Patricia的行为很疯狂{\r英文}\N"Patricia acted crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.69,0:18:21.23,中文,,0,0,0,,会有自杀的危险{\r英文}\N"Threatened she would kill herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.23,0:18:22.63,中文,,0,0,0,,她跳下去的时候是独自一人"{\r英文}\NWas alone when she jumped."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.63,0:18:24.20,中文,,0,0,0,,名字很熟{\r英文}\NFamiliar names.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.20,0:18:27.63,中文,,0,0,0,,没错 他们现在都被安排进了Hamilton的行政机关{\r英文}\NYeah, they've all been appointed positions in Hamilton's administration!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.73,0:18:29.37,中文,,0,0,0,,你认为我杀了你的妻子{\r英文}\NYou think I killed your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.37,0:18:32.37,中文,,0,0,0,,就因为我关照了几个兄弟会的朋友吗{\r英文}\Nbecause I did a couple of frat buddies some favors?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.37,0:18:34.91,中文,,0,0,0,,宾客名单上有你{\r英文}\NYou were on the guest list!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.91,0:18:38.58,中文,,0,0,0,,但警察却从没提问过你{\r英文}\NBut the cops never interviewed you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.58,0:18:41.61,中文,,0,0,0,,他从没提问过你{\r英文}\NHe never interviewed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.62,0:18:44.28,中文,,0,0,0,,因为我当时不在{\r英文}\NBecause I wasn't there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.29,0:18:46.35,中文,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉这么说{\r英文}\NAnd I'm sorry to say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:49.09,中文,,0,0,0,,但似乎是你的妻子出了问题{\r英文}\Nbut it sounds like your wife had some issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.09,0:18:50.59,中文,,0,0,0,,-不 不是这样的 -Doug{\r英文}\N- No, that is not true. - Doug...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.59,0:18:51.96,中文,,0,0,0,,-Doug 别激动 -不 我说的是{\r英文}\N- Doug, take it easy! - No, I'm saying--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.96,0:18:53.59,中文,,0,0,0,,遇到那种会迫使人{\r英文}\NLook, it's the type of thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.59,0:18:54.59,中文,,0,0,0,,做出错误决定的事情{\r英文}\Nwould force people to make a bad decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:18:56.83,中文,,0,0,0,,我留在家里带孩子{\r英文}\NI stayed at home with a baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.83,0:18:58.33,中文,,0,0,0,,这样她就能跟朋友出去{\r英文}\Nso she could go out with friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.33,0:18:59.57,中文,,0,0,0,,进行社交{\r英文}\Ndo some networking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.57,0:19:00.83,中文,,0,0,0,,那天是狂欢节{\r英文}\NIt was Mardi Gras.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.84,0:19:02.30,中文,,0,0,0,,我说"去吧 玩得开心点"{\r英文}\NI said, "Go, have some fun."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.30,0:19:03.77,中文,,0,0,0,,你知道吗{\r英文}\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.31,0:19:09.28,中文,,0,0,0,,接着你就出现在我家门口{\r英文}\NAnd then you showed up at my door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.35,0:19:19.35,中文,,0,0,0,,你在想什么 Mike{\r英文}\NWhat are you thinking, Mike?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.39,0:19:25.72,中文,,0,0,0,,我不想再玩游戏了{\r英文}\NI'm tired of playing games.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.80,0:19:31.53,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道我的权利{\r英文}\NI know my rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.53,0:19:33.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我什么也不会说的{\r英文}\NI'm not saying anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.17,中文,,0,0,0,,Angela Goodwin{\r英文}\NAngela Goodwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.17,0:19:36.77,中文,,0,0,0,,前科包括 持有违禁品{\r英文}\NPriors include possession
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.77,0:19:38.07,中文,,0,0,0,,教唆罪{\r英文}\Nand solicitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:39.67,中文,,0,0,0,,你现在要犯下阴谋罪{\r英文}\NYou're stepping it up to conspiracy,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.67,0:19:41.11,中文,,0,0,0,,绑架罪{\r英文}\Nkidnapping,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.11,0:19:42.71,中文,,0,0,0,,使用致命武器袭击罪{\r英文}\Nassault with a deadly weapon,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.71,0:19:44.01,中文,,0,0,0,,谋杀罪么{\r英文}\Nmurder?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.88,0:19:47.98,中文,,0,0,0,,他说那是个玩笑{\r英文}\NHe said it was a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.98,0:19:49.22,中文,,0,0,0,,谁{\r英文}\NWho?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.22,0:19:50.58,中文,,0,0,0,,有人付我五百美金{\r英文}\NThe guy who paid me $500 to flirt
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.59,0:19:52.15,中文,,0,0,0,,让我跟市长调情 让他落单{\r英文}\Nwith the Mayor and get him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.15,0:19:54.42,中文,,0,0,0,,让市长落单{\r英文}\NGetting the Mayor alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:57.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你不觉得奇怪吗{\r英文}\NThat didn't strike you as strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.16,0:19:58.89,中文,,0,0,0,,我接触过政客和他们的朋友{\r英文}\NI've spent time with politicians and their friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.89,0:20:00.49,中文,,0,0,0,,他们会做出奇怪的事{\r英文}\NThey do strange things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:03.03,中文,,0,0,0,,那人说{\r英文}\NLook, the guy said
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.03,0:20:04.66,中文,,0,0,0,,他是一个在搞恶作剧的兄弟会成员{\r英文}\Nhe was a fraternity brother playing a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:07.97,中文,,0,0,0,,不应该有人受伤的 我发誓{\r英文}\NNo one was supposed to get hurt, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.97,0:20:09.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他有告诉你他的名字么{\r英文}\NDid he tell you his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.24,0:20:10.64,中文,,0,0,0,,没有{\r英文}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:12.40,中文,,0,0,0,,他长什么样{\r英文}\NWhat'd he look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.41,0:20:13.94,中文,,0,0,0,,灰白的长发{\r英文}\NLong, graying hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:15.57,中文,,0,0,0,,很悲伤 但人不错{\r英文}\NSad, but nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.58,0:20:17.71,中文,,0,0,0,,他还留着胡子{\r英文}\NHe also had a beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.71,0:20:19.15,中文,,0,0,0,,我说的是事实{\r英文}\NI am telling you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:20.78,中文,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这个市长{\r英文}\NI like the Mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.78,0:20:22.55,中文,,0,0,0,,我还为他投票了{\r英文}\NI voted for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.35,0:20:27.69,中文,,0,0,0,,你的计划是什么 Mike{\r英文}\NWhat's the plan here, Mike?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.32,0:20:31.72,中文,,0,0,0,,你有一把枪{\r英文}\NYou've got that gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.73,0:20:33.19,中文,,0,0,0,,然后呢{\r英文}\Nand what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.83,0:20:36.63,中文,,0,0,0,,谋杀两个人吗{\r英文}\NMurder two people?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.63,0:20:38.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你不是那种人 Mike{\r英文}\NYou're not this man, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.20,0:20:40.07,中文,,0,0,0,,你以为你了解我么{\r英文}\NYou think you know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.07,0:20:42.13,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道你很生气{\r英文}\NKnow you're angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.14,0:20:43.74,中文,,0,0,0,,你女儿受到了伤害{\r英文}\NYour daughter's hurtin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:44.94,中文,,0,0,0,,你们都渴望{\r英文}\NBoth desperate
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.94,0:20:46.27,中文,,0,0,0,,得到答案{\r英文}\Nfor answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.27,0:20:47.61,中文,,0,0,0,,这个样子已经太久了{\r英文}\NBeen that way for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.61,0:20:48.81,中文,,0,0,0,,抱歉{\r英文}\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.61,0:20:51.28,中文,,0,0,0,,答案不会变的{\r英文}\NThat's not gonna change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.28,0:20:52.95,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride没找我谈{\r英文}\NPride never talked to me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.95,0:20:54.91,中文,,0,0,0,,因为我没有参加派对{\r英文}\Nbecause I was never at that party.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.79,0:21:06.79,中文,,0,0,0,,你确定吗 Douglas{\r英文}\NYou sure about that, Douglas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.23,0:21:10.83,中文,,0,0,0,,那是你{\r英文}\NThat's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.77,0:21:15.13,中文,,0,0,0,,你从哪儿弄来的{\r英文}\NWhere did you get this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.14,0:21:17.67,中文,,0,0,0,,法学院档案室{\r英文}\NLaw school archives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.67,0:21:19.64,中文,,0,0,0,,花了几年时间去找{\r英文}\NTook a couple years of digging,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.64,0:21:22.21,中文,,0,0,0,,但它就在那儿{\r英文}\Nbut it was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:24.14,中文,,0,0,0,,你说谎了{\r英文}\NYou lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.15,0:21:26.01,中文,,0,0,0,,在这个紧要关头{\r英文}\NWith everything that's at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.15,0:21:29.35,中文,,0,0,0,,真是太鲁莽了{\r英文}\NThat was damn reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.55,0:21:34.42,中文,,0,0,0,,Ran Angela对绑架犯的描述{\r英文}\NRan Angela's description of the kidnapper
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.42,0:21:36.82,中文,,0,0,0,,与酒店雇员记录对比 没有匹配的{\r英文}\Nthrough the hotel employee records. No luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.82,0:21:38.39,中文,,0,0,0,,派对来宾方面呢{\r英文}\NAnything on the party guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.39,0:21:40.26,中文,,0,0,0,,酒店保安还在看监控{\r英文}\NHotel security is still reviewing surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.26,0:21:42.96,中文,,0,0,0,,Angela提到了兄弟会恶作剧{\r英文}\NLook, Angela mentioned a fraternity prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.96,0:21:45.73,中文,,0,0,0,,有没有可能带走市长的人是在恶作剧呢{\r英文}\NIs there any chance whoever took the Mayor is pulling one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.73,0:21:48.10,中文,,0,0,0,,我在兄弟会时 有过很多恶作剧 有些是很疯狂的{\r英文}\NThere were a lot of pranks in my frat days, some crazy stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.10,0:21:50.04,中文,,0,0,0,,但我认为不会有人开这种玩笑{\r英文}\Nbut I doubt anyone would do something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.51,0:21:55.24,中文,,0,0,0,,-戊巴比妥 -Sebastian{\r英文}\N- Pentobarbital. - Sebastian?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:57.54,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿 我尽快赶到了实验室{\r英文}\NHey, yeah, I got to the lab as soon as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.55,0:21:59.65,中文,,0,0,0,,我是新克鲁的指定司机{\r英文}\NI'm designated driver for my new Krewe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.55,0:21:59.65,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}克鲁是一个在新奥尔良狂欢节最后一天主持庆祝活动的民间组织
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.65,0:22:02.85,中文,,0,0,0,,这是克鲁Livre{\r英文}\NIt's a Krewe Livre.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.85,0:22:04.25,中文,,0,0,0,,法语里"书"的意思{\r英文}\NThat's French for book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.25,0:22:05.62,中文,,0,0,0,,我们是读书俱乐部{\r英文}\NThey're-they're my book club.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.62,0:22:08.42,中文,,0,0,0,,我显然是马克·吐温 这位是{\r英文}\NI'm Mark Twain, obviously. This is, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:10.82,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰纳里·奥康纳 威廉·福克纳 杜鲁门·卡波特{\r英文}\NFlannery O'Connor, William Faulkner, Truman Capote...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:10.82,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}都是作家的名字
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.83,0:22:12.16,中文,,0,0,0,,戊巴比妥{\r英文}\NPentobarbital?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.16,0:22:13.83,中文,,0,0,0,,对 戊巴比妥{\r英文}\NYeah, pentobarbital.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.83,0:22:15.39,中文,,0,0,0,,我认为是这种药杀死了Alex下士{\r英文}\NI think it's the drug that killed Corporal Alex.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.40,0:22:16.93,中文,,0,0,0,,我是根据Lorretta发给我的{\r英文}\NI determined it based on the photos
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.93,0:22:18.73,中文,,0,0,0,,Alex眼睛的照片得出的结论{\r英文}\Nthat Loretta sent me of Alex's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.73,0:22:20.33,中文,,0,0,0,,眼球鼓起 肌肉坚硬{\r英文}\NThe swelling and muscle rigidity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.33,0:22:21.67,中文,,0,0,0,,其原因是过敏反应和...{\r英文}\Nwere caused by an allergic reaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.67,0:22:24.47,中文,,0,0,0,,-恶性高热症 -再多说点{\r英文}\N- malignant hyperthermia. - More, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.47,0:22:26.14,中文,,0,0,0,,那还是一种麻醉剂{\r英文}\NIt's, uh, it's also an anesthetic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.14,0:22:28.27,中文,,0,0,0,,用在注射死刑的注射液中{\r英文}\Nused in the cocktail for lethal injections.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.14,0:22:28.27,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}注射死刑 注射足以致命剂量的药剂使注射对象死亡的一种死刑
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.28,0:22:30.51,中文,,0,0,0,,还有{\r英文}\NAnd, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.51,0:22:32.85,中文,,0,0,0,,我现在正式害怕了{\r英文}\NI'm officially scared right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.85,0:22:35.38,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride对我来说就像爸爸一样{\r英文}\NI mean, Pride's like a dad to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.38,0:22:37.48,中文,,0,0,0,,哪怕他没有意识到这点{\r英文}\NEven if he doesn't realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.49,0:22:39.49,中文,,0,0,0,,也许他意识到了 他只是在做{\r英文}\NMaybe he does realize it and he's just doing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.49,0:22:41.12,中文,,0,0,0,,反向教养 就像阿提克斯·芬奇...{\r英文}\Na reverse parenting thing, like Atticus Finch before...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.49,0:22:41.12,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}哈珀李作品《杀死一只知更鸟》的主人公
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.12,0:22:42.45,中文,,0,0,0,,Sebastian{\r英文}\NSebastian.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:43.79,中文,,0,0,0,,呃 抱歉{\r英文}\NYeah, um... sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.79,0:22:46.33,中文,,0,0,0,,这种药是在配药房制成的{\r英文}\NThe drug is made at compounding pharmacies.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.33,0:22:48.59,中文,,0,0,0,,所以绑架犯可能在一个配药房工作{\r英文}\NSo our kidnapper could be working at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.60,0:22:50.63,中文,,0,0,0,,但麻烦在于有保密法{\r英文}\NWell, the twist is that there are secrecy laws
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.63,0:22:52.93,中文,,0,0,0,,保护注射死刑用药的供应商{\r英文}\Nthat shield lethal injection suppliers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.93,0:22:54.67,中文,,0,0,0,,雇员记录是对外保密的{\r英文}\NEmployee records are kept under wraps.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.67,0:22:57.10,中文,,0,0,0,,那我们不得不揭秘他们了{\r英文}\NWell, then, we'll have to unwrap them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.11,0:22:59.51,中文,,0,0,0,,有了 在海湾地区{\r英文}\NAll right, five pharmacies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.51,0:23:01.54,中文,,0,0,0,,有五间药房提供戊巴比妥{\r英文}\Nin the Gulf region provide pentobarbital.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.54,0:23:03.54,中文,,0,0,0,,我们需要调查这几间药店的员工名单{\r英文}\NWe need to check employee names of every one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.54,0:23:05.34,中文,,0,0,0,,看看是否有人和Pride或Hamilton有关联{\r英文}\Nand see if any of them connect with Pride or Hamilton.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.35,0:23:06.78,中文,,0,0,0,,到底{\r英文}\NWhat in the hell
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:08.51,中文,,0,0,0,,一个药剂师想从Pride那儿得到什么呢{\r英文}\Nwould a pharmacist want with Pride anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.52,0:23:10.02,中文,,0,0,0,,猜不到{\r英文}\NNo idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.02,0:23:11.42,中文,,0,0,0,,可能是他正在培养的一个兴趣{\r英文}\NCould be a developing interest
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.42,0:23:12.99,中文,,0,0,0,,只是还没机会告诉我们{\r英文}\Nhe never had a chance to tell us about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.99,0:23:14.32,中文,,0,0,0,,查到75个{\r英文}\NSeeing 75 employees
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.32,0:23:16.02,中文,,0,0,0,,有权接触到这种药的雇员{\r英文}\Nwho had clearance to handle the drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.02,0:23:19.19,中文,,0,0,0,,交叉比对NCIS的案件数据库 市长...{\r英文}\NCross-referencing NCIS cases, the Mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.19,0:23:20.86,中文,,0,0,0,,好 灰色轿车的情况呢{\r英文}\NAll right, what about that gray sedan?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.86,0:23:22.86,中文,,0,0,0,,部分车牌号为TSJ{\r英文}\NPartial license TSJ.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.86,0:23:24.70,中文,,0,0,0,,-正在检索车辆管理局记录 -很好{\r英文}\N- Checking DMV records. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.70,0:23:26.23,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们之中有人开这辆车{\r英文}\NBecause if one of them drives it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.23,0:23:28.87,中文,,0,0,0,,我们就离找到Pride更近一步了{\r英文}\Nwe're one step closer to finding Pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.87,0:23:30.80,中文,,0,0,0,,我为什么要相信你{\r英文}\NWhy did I even think to trust you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.81,0:23:32.57,中文,,0,0,0,,这个肯定经过图片处理{\r英文}\NIt must be photoshopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.57,0:23:34.24,中文,,0,0,0,,不是你想的那样{\r英文}\NIt's not what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.24,0:23:35.71,中文,,0,0,0,,三思 Douglas{\r英文}\NPick one, Douglas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.71,0:23:37.31,中文,,0,0,0,,他的意思是别再说谎了{\r英文}\NHe means stop lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.85,0:23:40.58,中文,,0,0,0,,别再说谎{\r英文}\NStop... lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.58,0:23:42.45,中文,,0,0,0,,-Mike... -认罪吧{\r英文}\N- Mike... - Confess!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.45,0:23:44.18,中文,,0,0,0,,-不 -Mike 等等{\r英文}\N- No! - Mike, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.19,0:23:45.98,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike{\r英文}\NMike!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.99,0:23:47.22,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike 别激动{\r英文}\NMike, take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.22,0:23:49.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你可以把这个交给地方检察官{\r英文}\NYou can take this to the D.A.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.26,0:23:50.79,中文,,0,0,0,,不行 地方检察官在两周前{\r英文}\NNo, the D.A. rejected a request
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.79,0:23:52.99,中文,,0,0,0,,已经拒绝重审此案了{\r英文}\Nto reopen the case two weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.99,0:23:54.29,中文,,0,0,0,,起来 起来{\r英文}\NGet up! Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.30,0:23:55.46,中文,,0,0,0,,-说啊 -Mike...{\r英文}\N- Say it! - Mike...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.46,0:23:57.20,中文,,0,0,0,,-你杀了她 说啊 -Mike{\r英文}\N- You killed her! Say it! - Mike!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.20,0:23:58.66,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike 这根本帮不了Stacey{\r英文}\NMike, this won't help Stacey.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.67,0:24:00.37,中文,,0,0,0,,不要这样 不要{\r英文}\NDon't do this. Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.37,0:24:01.77,中文,,0,0,0,,市长要认罪了{\r英文}\NThe Mayor's gonna confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.77,0:24:03.54,中文,,0,0,0,,认罪{\r英文}\NConfess!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.37,0:24:06.21,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧{\r英文}\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:07.67,中文,,0,0,0,,我当时在场{\r英文}\NI was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.75,0:24:31.82,中文,,0,0,0,,能接触到杀死Alex下士的药物的{\r英文}\NOf the pharmacists who had access
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.82,0:24:33.82,中文,,0,0,0,,药剂师中{\r英文}\Nto the drug that killed Corporal Alex,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.83,0:24:36.39,中文,,0,0,0,,只有一个人和Pride或Hamilton有关联{\r英文}\Nonly one had a connection to Pride or Hamilton.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.39,0:24:37.73,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike Spar{\r英文}\NMike Spar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.73,0:24:39.73,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar学的是医学和化学{\r英文}\NSpar studied medicine and chemistry
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.73,0:24:41.36,中文,,0,0,0,,在Hamilton的母校读的{\r英文}\Nat Hamilton's Alma mater.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.37,0:24:43.10,中文,,0,0,0,,他还有辆灰色的福特金牛座{\r英文}\NAnd he owns a gray Taurus,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.10,0:24:44.90,中文,,0,0,0,,有人看见Pride就是被塞进了这辆车{\r英文}\Nthe one Pride was seen taken away in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.90,0:24:46.84,中文,,0,0,0,,用他自己的车{\r英文}\NUses his own car...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.84,0:24:48.80,中文,,0,0,0,,我感觉不像是一个罪犯的思维啊{\r英文}\NDoesn't sound like a criminal mastermind to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:51.71,中文,,0,0,0,,还用注射死刑的用药来犯案{\r英文}\NUses a drug associated with lethal injection.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.71,0:24:53.74,中文,,0,0,0,,我感觉简直就是詹姆斯·邦德啊{\r英文}\NSounds pretty James Bond to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.75,0:24:55.61,中文,,0,0,0,,好了 他在Hamilton的母校上过学{\r英文}\NOkay, so he went to Hamilton's school.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.61,0:24:57.68,中文,,0,0,0,,那和Pride的联系又是什么呢{\r英文}\NWhat's the connection to Pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.68,0:25:01.88,中文,,0,0,0,,在Pride经手的NCIS案件中搜索Spar的名字{\r英文}\NRunning Spar's name against Pride's NCIS cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.89,0:25:03.32,中文,,0,0,0,,查不到{\r英文}\NNothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.32,0:25:05.55,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 我们追溯到更早以前{\r英文}\NAll right, let's go back farther than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.56,0:25:08.09,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride还在警局任职期间的老案子{\r英文}\NPride's old cases when he was working sheriff's deputy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.59,0:25:11.69,中文,,0,0,0,,找到了 在这儿{\r英文}\NGot 'em, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.70,0:25:13.66,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike Spar 他的妻子{\r英文}\NMike Spar. His wife committed...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.67,0:25:16.03,中文,,0,0,0,,在一个狂欢节派对上自杀了{\r英文}\Nsuicide at a Mardi Gras party.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.03,0:25:19.87,中文,,0,0,0,,Pride的警局档案中说 是他通知的Spar{\r英文}\NPride's JPSO report states that he notified Spar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.87,0:25:21.47,中文,,0,0,0,,好 找到关联了{\r英文}\NAll right, that's the connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.47,0:25:22.84,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar的雇员档案上{\r英文}\NSpar's employee record
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.84,0:25:24.74,中文,,0,0,0,,把他的女儿列为他的紧急联系人{\r英文}\Nlists his daughter as an emergency contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.74,0:25:26.08,中文,,0,0,0,,试着调查下她{\r英文}\NTrying to track her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.08,0:25:27.38,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar在Dauphine有个住处{\r英文}\NSpar has a place on Dauphine.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.38,0:25:28.88,中文,,0,0,0,,他女儿可能在那儿{\r英文}\NHis daughter could be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:30.65,中文,,0,0,0,,如果Pride和Hamilton还在这个城区{\r英文}\NIf Pride and Hamilton are still in the Quarter,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.65,0:25:32.55,中文,,0,0,0,,这是Mike Spar可能会带他们去的地方{\r英文}\Nit could be where Mike Spar took them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.55,0:25:34.75,中文,,0,0,0,,我们接近真相了 我去联系特警队到那儿汇合{\r英文}\NWe're closer. I'll have SWAT meet me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.55,0:25:34.75,注解,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Special Weapons and Tactics
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.95,0:25:38.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你说谎要么是因为你杀了她{\r英文}\NYou either lied because you killed her
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.26,0:25:40.46,中文,,0,0,0,,要么就是你在保护某人{\r英文}\Nor you're protecting someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.46,0:25:42.12,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 你现在成法官和陪审团了么{\r英文}\NOh, y-you're judge and jury now?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.13,0:25:43.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我只是个警察{\r英文}\NJust a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.36,0:25:44.93,中文,,0,0,0,,在做一个警察在很久以前{\r英文}\NDoing what the cops should have done
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.93,0:25:46.60,中文,,0,0,0,,就应该做的事情{\r英文}\Na long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.43,0:25:49.90,中文,,0,0,0,,所以 狂欢节那晚{\r英文}\NSo, Mardi Gras night,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.90,0:25:51.27,中文,,0,0,0,,25年前{\r英文}\N25 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.27,0:25:52.47,中文,,0,0,0,,救命啊{\r英文}\NHelp!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.47,0:25:54.10,中文,,0,0,0,,来人救我{\r英文}\NSomebody help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.11,0:25:56.57,中文,,0,0,0,,救命啊{\r英文}\NHelp me!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.71,0:25:58.97,中文,,0,0,0,,没有人能听见{\r英文}\NNo one can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.98,0:26:00.88,中文,,0,0,0,,Mardi Gras那晚{\r英文}\NMardi Gras night.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.88,0:26:02.95,中文,,0,0,0,,告诉我发生了什么{\r英文}\NTell me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.38,0:26:08.98,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧{\r英文}\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.02,0:26:12.82,中文,,0,0,0,,那天晚上我在那儿{\r英文}\NI was there that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.76,0:26:16.39,中文,,0,0,0,,但我没看见{\r英文}\NBut I did not see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.39,0:26:18.79,中文,,0,0,0,,他妻子发生了什么{\r英文}\Nwhat happened to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.80,0:26:20.80,中文,,0,0,0,,我走得很早 我发誓{\r英文}\NI left early, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.80,0:26:21.83,中文,,0,0,0,,你为什么撒谎呢{\r英文}\NWhy'd you lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.83,0:26:24.97,中文,,0,0,0,,那种派对{\r英文}\NA party like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.97,0:26:26.64,中文,,0,0,0,,死了个女孩的地方{\r英文}\NWhere a girl dies?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.64,0:26:28.90,中文,,0,0,0,,对有政治抱负的人来说 不是件好事{\r英文}\NNot good, if you've got any political ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.91,0:26:30.54,中文,,0,0,0,,继续{\r英文}\NMore.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.54,0:26:32.17,中文,,0,0,0,,你有所隐瞒{\r英文}\NYou're hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.18,0:26:34.14,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道你参加了那个派对{\r英文}\NI know you were at that party.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.15,0:26:35.81,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道你说了谎{\r英文}\NI know you lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.81,0:26:38.05,中文,,0,0,0,,我们离开这里{\r英文}\NWe get out of here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.05,0:26:40.52,中文,,0,0,0,,我就会去调查原因{\r英文}\NI'll figure out why.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.06,0:26:51.49,中文,,0,0,0,,当时{\r英文}\NThere was...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.50,0:26:54.00,中文,,0,0,0,,有个仪式 算是吧{\r英文}\Na ritual, of sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.00,0:26:56.17,中文,,0,0,0,,不能公开的那种{\r英文}\NBehind closed doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.17,0:26:57.93,中文,,0,0,0,,你听说过那些事情{\r英文}\NYou've heard the stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.94,0:27:01.37,中文,,0,0,0,,但要是有人知道我当时在那里的话{\r英文}\NAnd if anybody knew I was there...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.37,0:27:04.44,中文,,0,0,0,,我就完蛋了{\r英文}\NI mean, I would be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.44,0:27:06.24,中文,,0,0,0,,你说了25年的谎{\r英文}\NYou lied for 25 years
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.24,0:27:08.21,中文,,0,0,0,,就因为你参与了一个见不得人的兄弟会仪式{\r英文}\Nbecause you were part of a sick fraternity ritual?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.21,0:27:09.61,中文,,0,0,0,,更像是{\r英文}\NMore like
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.61,0:27:13.38,中文,,0,0,0,,你被困扰了25年 Spar先生{\r英文}\Nyou were obsessed for 25 years, Mr. Spar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.38,0:27:15.55,中文,,0,0,0,,不是我{\r英文}\NNot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.55,0:27:17.02,中文,,0,0,0,,我当时不得不放下此事{\r英文}\NI had to put this away.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.02,0:27:19.02,中文,,0,0,0,,进入Spar的住处 待命{\r英文}\NEntering Spar's house. Stand by.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.02,0:27:20.69,中文,,0,0,0,,把注意力放在女儿身上{\r英文}\NFocus on my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.69,0:27:24.99,中文,,0,0,0,,可是{\r英文}\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.00,0:27:27.83,中文,,0,0,0,,Stacey{\r英文}\NStacey...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.83,0:27:30.33,中文,,0,0,0,,她却对此不能释怀{\r英文}\Nshe was the one who couldn't move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.80,0:27:35.07,中文,,0,0,0,,她一定要知道真相{\r英文}\NShe had to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.07,0:27:37.87,中文,,0,0,0,,我跟她说 妈妈死于一起交通事故{\r英文}\NI told her her mother died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.21,0:27:41.78,中文,,0,0,0,,但她听到了流言{\r英文}\NShe heard rumors and...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.55,0:27:45.65,中文,,0,0,0,,我让她别在意{\r英文}\NI told her to ignore them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.65,0:27:47.25,中文,,0,0,0,,随它去吧{\r英文}\NLet it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.25,0:27:49.29,中文,,0,0,0,,可她就是那种...{\r英文}\NShe was the one who-who...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.29,0:27:51.02,中文,,0,0,0,,非要查个水落石出的人{\r英文}\Nspearheaded all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.02,0:27:52.62,中文,,0,0,0,,是的{\r英文}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.73,0:27:57.56,中文,,0,0,0,,她所看到的{\r英文}\N{\i1}What she saw...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.56,0:27:59.83,中文,,0,0,0,,她承受不了{\r英文}\N{\i1}it was too much for her.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.83,0:28:03.23,中文,,0,0,0,,她开始麻木自我{\r英文}\N{\i1}She started numbing herself,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.23,0:28:05.20,中文,,0,0,0,,酗酒成瘾{\r英文}\N{\i1}drinking too much,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.20,0:28:06.87,中文,,0,0,0,,沾染毒品{\r英文}\N{\i1}getting into drugs.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.17,0:28:11.07,中文,,0,0,0,,我必须帮她{\r英文}\NI had to help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.08,0:28:14.54,中文,,0,0,0,,她放不下 是吗{\r英文}\NShe took it on, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.55,0:28:16.05,中文,,0,0,0,,没办法{\r英文}\NHad to.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.05,0:28:17.65,中文,,0,0,0,,对{\r英文}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.62,0:28:22.79,中文,,0,0,0,,当你被抛弃了 有必要知道真相{\r英文}\NWhen you're abandoned, there's a need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.16,0:28:27.46,中文,,0,0,0,,现在我们来破这个案子{\r英文}\NNow we're going to work this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.86,0:28:31.26,中文,,0,0,0,,我们要为Stacey查明真相{\r英文}\NWe're gonna work this for Stacey.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.73,0:28:35.13,中文,,0,0,0,,Mike 你在这些档案里{\r英文}\NMike, what you found in those files...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.13,0:28:36.67,中文,,0,0,0,,发现的证据{\r英文}\Nthe evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.67,0:28:38.50,中文,,0,0,0,,Patricia的伤{\r英文}\NPatricia's injuries--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.50,0:28:40.40,中文,,0,0,0,,有打斗的痕迹吗{\r英文}\Nany signs of a struggle?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.40,0:28:42.97,中文,,0,0,0,,警察 他们没在意这件事{\r英文}\NCops, uh, didn't focus on any of that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.97,0:28:45.77,中文,,0,0,0,,但我们在意{\r英文}\NBut we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.78,0:28:47.31,中文,,0,0,0,,来吧{\r英文}\NNow, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.31,0:28:50.01,中文,,0,0,0,,证明那些假设{\r英文}\NProve the hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.01,0:28:51.91,中文,,0,0,0,,我开始给Alex下士进行尸检的时候{\r英文}\NWhile I start the autopsy on Corporal Alex,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.92,0:28:54.52,中文,,0,0,0,,-我希望你能看一下这些 -好的 是什么{\r英文}\N- I want you to take a look at these. - Okay, what are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.52,0:28:56.45,中文,,0,0,0,,是Brody在Mike Spar家里{\r英文}\NWell, they're photos Brody found
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.45,0:28:58.09,中文,,0,0,0,,发现的照片{\r英文}\Nin Mike Spar's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.09,0:29:00.92,中文,,0,0,0,,似乎是Spar和他的女儿{\r英文}\NIt appears Spar and his daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.93,0:29:03.43,中文,,0,0,0,,在调查他妻子自杀一案{\r英文}\Nwere investigating his wife's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.43,0:29:04.96,中文,,0,0,0,,恩{\r英文}\NHuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.10,0:29:08.53,中文,,0,0,0,,那儿{\r英文}\NThere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.53,0:29:10.74,中文,,0,0,0,,割伤 颈部断裂 是坠落造成的{\r英文}\NCuts, broken neck-- that speaks to the fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.74,0:29:11.23,中文,,0,0,0,,恩{\r英文}\NHuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.23,0:29:14.10,中文,,0,0,0,,这处螺旋形骨折则不是{\r英文}\NThis spiral fracture doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.11,0:29:16.11,中文,,0,0,0,,坠落事件通常不会出现螺旋形骨折{\r英文}\NSpiral fractures usually don't happen in falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.11,0:29:19.61,中文,,0,0,0,,更像是 工业事故{\r英文}\NMore like... industrial accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.61,0:29:22.95,中文,,0,0,0,,或是有人... 在打斗中扭断了别人的手臂{\r英文}\NOr when someone... twists someone else's arm in a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.28,0:29:26.05,中文,,0,0,0,,也许在Patricia从阳台掉落前{\r英文}\NMaybe Patricia struggled with someone
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.05,0:29:27.98,中文,,0,0,0,,和某人有过搏斗{\r英文}\Nbefore she went over the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.99,0:29:29.85,中文,,0,0,0,,或者她是被推下去的{\r英文}\NOr she was pushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.69,0:29:32.66,中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得是谋杀吗{\r英文}\NYou think she was murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.59,0:29:37.96,中文,,0,0,0,,Douglas{\r英文}\NDouglas...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.96,0:29:39.83,中文,,0,0,0,,说出真相吧{\r英文}\Ntell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.63,0:29:45.30,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他拿走那玩意儿 就轻松多了{\r英文}\NWell, it'd be a whole lot easier if he got rid of that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.35,0:30:02.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我离开派对时{\r英文}\NWhen I left the party,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.25,0:30:05.45,中文,,0,0,0,,我好像记得{\r英文}\NI might've remembered
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.46,0:30:08.62,中文,,0,0,0,,看到有人和他老婆在一起{\r英文}\Nseeing some guys with his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.63,0:30:10.26,中文,,0,0,0,,仪式的一部分吗{\r英文}\NPart of the ritual?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.93,0:30:14.66,中文,,0,0,0,,让她落单 把她灌醉{\r英文}\NGet her alone, get her drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.67,0:30:16.40,中文,,0,0,0,,她和他们打了起来{\r英文}\NShe fights them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.40,0:30:18.53,中文,,0,0,0,,我说了 我很早离开了{\r英文}\NI told you I left early.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.54,0:30:19.84,中文,,0,0,0,,等等{\r英文}\NWait.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.84,0:30:22.50,中文,,0,0,0,,那个{\r英文}\NThe...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.51,0:30:24.44,中文,,0,0,0,,项链{\r英文}\Nnecklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.44,0:30:28.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你看到她的时候 她戴着项链吗{\r英文}\NWhen you saw her, was she wearing a necklace?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.18,0:30:30.85,中文,,0,0,0,,有个坠子{\r英文}\NA pendant...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.85,0:30:32.58,中文,,0,0,0,,玫瑰形状的{\r英文}\Nin the shape of a rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.58,0:30:33.58,中文,,0,0,0,,我不记得了{\r英文}\NI don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.58,0:30:34.55,中文,,0,0,0,,在警方报告里{\r英文}\NIt-it's not mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.55,0:30:35.58,中文,,0,0,0,,没有提到{\r英文}\Nin the police report.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.59,0:30:37.02,中文,,0,0,0,,那晚她戴着项链吗{\r英文}\NShe was wearing one that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.02,0:30:38.05,中文,,0,0,0,,Stacey出生那晚{\r英文}\NI bought it for her
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.06,0:30:39.15,中文,,0,0,0,,我给她买的{\r英文}\Nthe night our Stacey was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.16,0:30:40.36,中文,,0,0,0,,她从来没有摘下过{\r英文}\NShe never took it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.36,0:30:41.72,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 等等 等下{\r英文}\NOh, wait, hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.73,0:30:44.03,中文,,0,0,0,,等一下{\r英文}\NOne second.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.03,0:30:45.66,中文,,0,0,0,,那个项链{\r英文}\NAll right, that necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.66,0:30:48.66,中文,,0,0,0,,玫瑰... 有颗蓝宝石吗{\r英文}\NThe rose, what... did it have a sapphire?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.67,0:30:51.03,中文,,0,0,0,,对{\r英文}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.37,0:30:53.77,中文,,0,0,0,,你拿走了吗{\r英文}\NDid you take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.77,0:30:55.34,中文,,0,0,0,,不是{\r英文}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.34,0:30:57.94,中文,,0,0,0,,但我想我知道是谁做的了{\r英文}\NBut I think I know who did.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.58,0:31:01.21,中文,,0,0,0,,天啊{\r英文}\NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.21,0:31:03.35,中文,,0,0,0,,这份报纸上的调查照片{\r英文}\NThis newspaper photo of the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.35,0:31:04.65,中文,,0,0,0,,你从盖着白布的尸体上{\r英文}\NWell, you're not gonna get much
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.65,0:31:06.15,中文,,0,0,0,,是得不到太多信息的{\r英文}\Nout of that body with the sheet on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.15,0:31:08.05,中文,,0,0,0,,不 不是尸体 是这个{\r英文}\NNo, it's not the body. It's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.05,0:31:10.82,中文,,0,0,0,,尸体旁边的地毯上有个标志{\r英文}\NThis is a logo on the carpet near the body
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.82,0:31:13.06,中文,,0,0,0,,是以前Alistair酒店的标志{\r英文}\Nof the old Alistair Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.06,0:31:14.62,中文,,0,0,0,,Alistair 我从没听过{\r英文}\NThe Alistair-- I never heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.63,0:31:16.49,中文,,0,0,0,,是 因为它很多年前就关了{\r英文}\NYeah, 'cause it closed years and years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.49,0:31:19.70,中文,,0,0,0,,老板拆毁了酒店 但有一部分完整保留了{\r英文}\NThe owners gutted it, but left some of it intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.70,0:31:21.23,中文,,0,0,0,,他们在这个地方建了什么{\r英文}\NWhat did they build in its place?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.23,0:31:24.97,中文,,0,0,0,,原址和附近建造了Landon Court酒店{\r英文}\NThe Landon Court Hotel on top of and around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.97,0:31:27.44,中文,,0,0,0,,那正是市长派对的举办地{\r英文}\NThat's-that's where the Mayor's party is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.44,0:31:29.10,中文,,0,0,0,,没人能够弄明白{\r英文}\NAnd no one can figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.11,0:31:31.61,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar是怎么把市长带走的{\r英文}\Nhow Spar got the Mayor out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.24,0:31:34.84,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们没有离开过呢{\r英文}\NWhat if they never left?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.85,0:31:36.61,中文,,0,0,0,,他以某种方式控制了市长{\r英文}\NHe-he-he somehow restrains the Mayor,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.61,0:31:37.91,中文,,0,0,0,,然后去抓Pride{\r英文}\Ngoes and gets Pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.92,0:31:39.55,中文,,0,0,0,,再回到犯罪现场{\r英文}\Nthen returns to the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.55,0:31:41.38,中文,,0,0,0,,她妻子25年前去世的地方{\r英文}\NWhere his wife died 25 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.39,0:31:42.82,中文,,0,0,0,,Sebastian{\r英文}\NSebastian...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.59,0:31:45.05,中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得Hamilton和Pride{\r英文}\NI think Hamilton and Pride
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.06,0:31:47.82,中文,,0,0,0,,还在那家酒店的某个地方{\r英文}\Nare still somewhere in that hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.09,0:31:50.53,中文,,0,0,0,,直到他说起项链{\r英文}\NI... I didn't make the connection
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.53,0:31:53.26,中文,,0,0,0,,我才联系起来的{\r英文}\Ntill he said the thing about the necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.26,0:31:57.17,中文,,0,0,0,,几年前 我和几个人在打扑克牌{\r英文}\NA couple years ago, I was playing poker with some guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.17,0:31:58.63,中文,,0,0,0,,兄弟会的吗{\r英文}\NFraternity brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.27,0:32:03.57,中文,,0,0,0,,其中有个人说起一条项链{\r英文}\NAnd one of them talked about a necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.57,0:32:05.11,中文,,0,0,0,,将其称为他的战利品{\r英文}\NCalled it his trophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.11,0:32:07.31,中文,,0,0,0,,说它代表了 只要你认识对的人{\r英文}\NSaid it represented what you can get away with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.31,0:32:09.11,中文,,0,0,0,,你就可以逍遥法外{\r英文}\Nif you know the right people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.11,0:32:10.78,中文,,0,0,0,,你知道项链在哪儿吗{\r英文}\NYou know where the necklace is?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.78,0:32:12.82,中文,,0,0,0,,恩{\r英文}\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.82,0:32:15.45,中文,,0,0,0,,谁拿了它{\r英文}\NWho has it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.09,0:32:18.39,中文,,0,0,0,,谁杀了我老婆{\r英文}\NWho killed my wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.16,0:32:23.03,中文,,0,0,0,,你先放了我们{\r英文}\NNot until you let us go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.70,0:32:25.66,中文,,0,0,0,,Douglas{\r英文}\NDouglas!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.66,0:32:27.00,中文,,0,0,0,,不要讨价还价{\r英文}\NNot a negotiation!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.00,0:32:29.20,中文,,0,0,0,,谁拿着它{\r英文}\NWho has it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.20,0:32:31.03,中文,,0,0,0,,告诉我{\r英文}\NTell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.97,0:32:35.40,中文,,0,0,0,,不然Pride探员就得死{\r英文}\NOr Agent Pride dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.98,0:32:57.91,中文,,0,0,0,,这是以前Alistair酒店的地图{\r英文}\NThis map is of the old Alistair Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.92,0:33:00.55,中文,,0,0,0,,酒店里的酒店么{\r英文}\NA... a hotel within a hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.55,0:33:03.25,中文,,0,0,0,,这是验尸员的推论吗{\r英文}\NThis is the medical examiner's theory?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.25,0:33:04.99,中文,,0,0,0,,你有更好的想法吗{\r英文}\NYou got a better one?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.99,0:33:07.49,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar付钱给女孩{\r英文}\NAll right, Spar pays the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.49,0:33:08.92,中文,,0,0,0,,她去勾引Hamilton{\r英文}\NAnd she lures Hamilton.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.93,0:33:10.89,中文,,0,0,0,,然后Spar袭击他{\r英文}\NAnd then Spar attacks him
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.89,0:33:12.66,中文,,0,0,0,,把他拉进服务通道{\r英文}\Nand pulls him into this service entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.66,0:33:14.23,中文,,0,0,0,,对 所以储藏室就是{\r英文}\NAll right, so the storage closet where
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.23,0:33:15.66,中文,,0,0,0,,Alex下士尸体被发现的地方 看上去{\r英文}\NCorporal Alex's body was found, it looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.67,0:33:17.77,中文,,0,0,0,,在这儿后面有什么通道{\r英文}\Nthere's some kind of tunnel behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.77,0:33:20.60,中文,,0,0,0,,但解释不了Spar是怎么抓住Pride探员的{\r英文}\NBut that doesn't explain how Spar got to Agent Pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.60,0:33:22.30,中文,,0,0,0,,这可能是... Patton最终发现一个线索{\r英文}\NThis might-- Patton finally got a hit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.31,0:33:24.11,中文,,0,0,0,,这辆灰色轿车离开了酒吧{\r英文}\Non the gray sedan seen leaving the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.11,0:33:26.68,中文,,0,0,0,,停在麦迪逊大街{\r英文}\NIt's parked on Madison Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.68,0:33:28.31,中文,,0,0,0,,那儿有一个旧的服务通道{\r英文}\NWell, there's an old service entrance there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.31,0:33:29.34,中文,,0,0,0,,对{\r英文}\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.35,0:33:31.01,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar控制住了Hamilton{\r英文}\NSpar restrains Hamilton,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.02,0:33:33.35,中文,,0,0,0,,由服务通道离开 去抓Pride{\r英文}\Nleaves through the service entrance to get Pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.35,0:33:35.15,中文,,0,0,0,,把他带回来 趁着狂欢节的混乱{\r英文}\Nbrings him back, chaos of Mardi Gras,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.15,0:33:36.62,中文,,0,0,0,,没有人知道{\r英文}\Nno one's the wiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.62,0:33:38.19,中文,,0,0,0,,计划还算完美{\r英文}\NIt was kind of the perfect plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.19,0:33:40.19,中文,,0,0,0,,为了什么 把Pride和市长{\r英文}\NTo what-- taking Pride and the Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.19,0:33:41.66,中文,,0,0,0,,带回他妻子自杀的地点{\r英文}\Nback to the scene of his wife's suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.66,0:33:42.92,中文,,0,0,0,,那人脑子有病{\r英文}\NGuy's a psychopath.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.93,0:33:44.29,中文,,0,0,0,,我们得把事情处理好{\r英文}\NOkay, we got to do this right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.30,0:33:45.93,中文,,0,0,0,,有什么人是这家伙信任的 家人有吗{\r英文}\NIs there anybody this guys trusts? Family?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.93,0:33:48.03,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他跟我们联系了 我们找谁去跟他谈{\r英文}\NAnyone we can get to talk to him, if he makes contact?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.03,0:33:50.33,中文,,0,0,0,,他有个女儿 我们正试图和她取得联系{\r英文}\NHe's got a daughter and we are trying to get in touch with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.33,0:33:52.37,中文,,0,0,0,,你需要我{\r英文}\NYou need me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.37,0:33:54.60,中文,,0,0,0,,要我帮忙 就不能伤害他{\r英文}\NAnd I'm not doing anything without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.61,0:33:56.20,中文,,0,0,0,,说吧{\r英文}\NTell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.17,0:33:59.71,中文,,0,0,0,,听着 Mike{\r英文}\NListen, Mike...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.71,0:34:02.28,中文,,0,0,0,,我的确不是一个好父亲{\r英文}\NGod knows I'm no authority on parenting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.28,0:34:03.98,中文,,0,0,0,,但从你身上 我能学到一些事{\r英文}\NBut I could learn a thing or two from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.98,0:34:05.88,中文,,0,0,0,,真的{\r英文}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.88,0:34:07.95,中文,,0,0,0,,比方说 把孩子的幸福放在首位{\r英文}\NLike putting my kid's welfare before mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.95,0:34:10.52,中文,,0,0,0,,正如你为Stacey所做的一样{\r英文}\NJust like you did with Stacey.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.52,0:34:11.99,中文,,0,0,0,,够了{\r英文}\NStop.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.99,0:34:13.72,中文,,0,0,0,,她就是我们此刻在这里的原因{\r英文}\NShe's the reason why we're here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.72,0:34:16.59,中文,,0,0,0,,她也是你必须放我们走的理由{\r英文}\NAnd she's the reason why you need to let us go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.59,0:34:18.63,中文,,0,0,0,,别说了{\r英文}\NStop.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.96,0:34:22.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你不想再见到Stacay吗{\r英文}\NDon't you want to see Stacey again?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.17,0:34:24.33,中文,,0,0,0,,我再也见不到她了{\r英文}\NNever gonna see her again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.20,0:34:28.07,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么{\r英文}\NWhy not?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.74,0:34:31.87,中文,,0,0,0,,她死了 对吗{\r英文}\NShe's dead, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.75,0:34:36.75,中文,,0,0,0,,坏消息{\r英文}\N{\i1}Bad news.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.75,0:34:39.15,中文,,0,0,0,,Spar的女儿因吸毒过量而死{\r英文}\NSpar's daughter died of a drug overdose.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.15,0:34:40.22,中文,,0,0,0,,什么时候{\r英文}\NWhen?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.22,0:34:41.38,中文,,0,0,0,,两个礼拜前{\r英文}\NTwo weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.39,0:34:42.75,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 谢谢{\r英文}\NAll right, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.75,0:34:44.85,中文,,0,0,0,,他女儿死了 吸毒过度{\r英文}\NDaughter's dead. Drug overdose.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.86,0:34:46.76,中文,,0,0,0,,没有家人可以说服Spar了吗{\r英文}\NSo no family to talk Spar down?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.76,0:34:47.99,中文,,0,0,0,,没了 只能靠我们自己{\r英文}\NNope, it's up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.99,0:34:49.39,中文,,0,0,0,,Percy和我负责地道{\r英文}\NAll right, Percy and I will take the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.39,0:34:51.73,中文,,0,0,0,,Tate 你负责服务通道{\r英文}\NTate, you got the service entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.73,0:34:53.93,中文,,0,0,0,,明白{\r英文}\NCopy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.47,0:35:01.77,中文,,0,0,0,,他就没打算放我们走{\r英文}\NHe was never gonna let us go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.77,0:35:04.37,中文,,0,0,0,,改变计划{\r英文}\NChange the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.38,0:35:07.31,中文,,0,0,0,,从一开始就是自杀性任务{\r英文}\NIt's been a suicide mission from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.31,0:35:09.01,中文,,0,0,0,,改变计划 Douglas{\r英文}\NChange it, Douglas.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.01,0:35:10.18,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么变{\r英文}\NHow?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.18,0:35:12.25,中文,,0,0,0,,谁拿了项链{\r英文}\NWho has the necklace?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.75,0:35:16.05,中文,,0,0,0,,谁杀了Patricia{\r英文}\NWho killed Patricia?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.05,0:35:18.09,中文,,0,0,0,,名字 告诉他{\r英文}\NA name-- give him...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.09,0:35:19.55,中文,,0,0,0,,告诉他名字{\r英文}\Ngive him a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.56,0:35:22.49,中文,,0,0,0,,政治自杀 Dwayne{\r英文}\NPolitical suicide, Dwayne.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.49,0:35:23.99,中文,,0,0,0,,实实在在的自杀{\r英文}\NAn actual suicide.
